# core-service

Express + `@ts-rest/express`. Business logic lives in DAOs, not routes.

## Route handlers (`src/routes/`)

```typescript
type CreateTestRoute = AppRouteImplementation<typeof contract.createTest>;

export const createTestRoute: CreateTestRoute = async ({ body }) => {
  const created = await new TestsDAO().create(body);
  return { status: 201, body: convertToResponseBody(created) };
};
```

- Map DB entities → contract response shapes in local `convertToResponseBody` helpers.
- Return `{ status: 404, body: {} }` for not found; validation errors throw `ValidationError` (→ 400).
- Type alias at bottom of file: `AppRouteImplementation<typeof contract.x>`.

## DAOs (`src/db/`)

- Class per table/domain; optional `db` constructor param for transactions.
- Use Drizzle tables from `@total-report/core-schema/schema`.
- Shared DB connection: `src/db/setup.ts`.
- Validation in `src/validations/validations.ts`; domain errors in `src/errors/errors.ts`.

## Auth utils

- `src/middleware/auth.ts` — JWT Bearer verification
- `src/utils/auth-utils.ts` — token/password hashing
- `src/utils/user-access.ts` — `canUseSystem(user)`
